node.text:
❤️
——
👇🏼 INGREDIENTS:
💥 ASSEMBLY
- 1 1/2 tablespoon melted butter
- 1 slightly beaten egg
- 1/2 cup peanut butter
- 1 1/2 cups almond milk
- 1 tablespoon honey or maple syrup
- 1 1/2 cups old fashioned rolled oats
- 1/2 teaspoon baking powder
- 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon
- 1/8 teaspoon salt
- 1/4 cup of strawberry or raspberry jam/jelly
——
👇🏼 INSTRUCTIONS:
- Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Grease a large skillet or 8x8 inch baking pan with coconut oil or generously spray with nonstick cooking spray.
- In a large bowl, add in melted and cooled coconut oil, peanut butter, honey, egg and almond milk. Whisk together until well combined and no large lumps of peanut butter remain.
- Fold in oats, baking powder, cinnamon and salt. Pour into prepared skillet/pan and make sure oatmeal is evenly spread out.
- Drop jam by teaspoonful onto oatmeal bake, then very gently swirl.
- Bake for 30-35 minutes until barely golden brown.
- DIG IN WITH A SPOON❗
🎥: @dessertbae
📍: Orlando, Florida
🎵: "King" Jef
👇🏽TAG SOMEONE WHO LOVES PB&J👇🏽

node.text:
HOMEMADE BIRTHDAY CAKE TRUFFLES‼️ 🎂🥳🔥 Are you making this next party or birthday⁉️ 🙌🏽🎉 #dessertbae ❤
⁣
💥INGREDIENTS:
- Box birthday cake mix (plus ingredients listed on the box to prepare the cake)
- 1/2 cup cream cheese (softened)
- 2 Cup white chocolate (melted)
- Mix colorful sprinkles
⁣
✨INSTRUCTIONS:
- Prepare the 9 x 13 inch cake according to package instructions, let it cool completely then crumble the cake in a food processor and process untill fine.
- Add softened cream cheese and process once more.
- Roll about 1 heaping tablespoon of the mixture into balls and place on a baking sheet lined with a parchment paper. You will get about 15-20 balls. Set in the fridge to chill.
- Melt white chocolate, remove cake balls form the fridge and using a fork dip them into melted chocolate. Place one ball at a time into the melted chocolate, roll the ball to coat evenly coat with the chocolate, then slightly tap the fork against the side of the bowl to trim the excess chocolate and topped them off with the colorful sprinkles. Set them back in the fridge until chocolate is firm. ENJOY! 😉
⁣
🎥: @dessertbae
👇🏽TAG SOMEONE WHO LOVES BIRTHDAY CAKE👇🏽

MINI NUTELLA & OREO CHEESECAKES 😍‼️ 🍫😋These have an Oreo base, with a Nutella cheesecake filling, topped with Oreo crumbs 🤤 Plus you only need 6 ingredients to make them 🔥 Would you SMASH or PASS⁉️ 😏#dessertbae ❤
⁣
💥INGREDIENTS💥
➡️BASE:
- 1 cup of crushed @OREO 
- 1/4 cup melted butter
➡️CHEESECAKE:
- 1 cup heavy cream
- 1 1/2 cups cream cheese
- 1/2 cup @nutella
- 1 cup icing sugar
➡️TOPPING:
- Crushed OREO's
⁣
🎥: @dessertbae
🎵: Music: Kumasi Musician: Jeff Kaale
👇🏽TAG SOMEONE WHO LOVES OREOS👇🏽

G•I•V•E•A•W•A•Y TIME‼️ ☕🎉⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
Who wants to win FREE COFFEE of selected @crukafe brew⁉️ 
⁣⁣⁣
1️⃣ To enter, follow: ⁣⁣
@crukafe
@dessertbae
⁣
2️⃣ Like this post & Tag your friends! (Multiple entries allowed), bonus if you repost in stories - Good luck!!!! ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣
3️⃣ Contestants must post a photo, video or reel of their iced coffee CRUation and tag @crukafe . (1) lucky person will win a free stock of their selected CRU brew! Contestants will have 48 hours to post their iced coffee CRUation. Get creative with your iced coffee! This can include:

Making fun designs on top

Interesting toppers

Tieing in sustainability + tase + aesthetic

Must follow and tag @crukafe and @dessertbae, and use hashtag #JoinTheCRU

*Must be 21 years or older and a resident of the US. This is not sponsored or endorsed by Facebook or Instagram. Winner picked and announced by 9/1/21
